subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Distinguished by the following set of features: antennal segment II in males thicker than segment I (
Figs 60
, 
92
); pronotum with distinct, yellow swelling along lateral margin (
Figs 44, 45
); corium with yellow patch medially (
Figs 44, 45
); endosoma with es1 short, cylindrical and without denticles at basal two thirds, apical one third broadened and serrate; es2 long, arcuate, weakly broadened and serrate apically; es3 long, tapering toward apex, its margins weakly sinuate; es4 with basal one sixth thin, nearly cylindrical, rest of the sclerite with dextrolateral margin arcuate and sinistrolateral margin strongly arcuate (
Fig. 97
); left paramere with sensory lobe moderately developed (
Figs 98, 99
).
